td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/04c49390-d091-c456-8c8d-5c86dcd7e97c.png\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/04c49390-d091-c456-8c8d-5c86dcd7e97c.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:298px;width:298px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-748\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b748\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>🙌<strong> </strong>Y’all crushed the last<strong> Melvin </strong>Method IPA - new brew incoming!</p><p>• <strong>Method Krush </strong>West Coast IPA with Krush hops</p><p>*expected Friday*</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b734\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-733\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b733\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Hot Crowler &amp; Growler Fills<p>Finback Social Fabric Hazy DIPA</p><p>Alternate Ending Royal Rug German Pilsner</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b599\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b579\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/a23a8e23-99fc-13ba-bb7b-697f702958c5.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/a23a8e23-99fc-13ba-bb7b-697f702958c5.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-723\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b723\"><table id=\"section_6566b84570996dc24b57f11073ef3730\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--45\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-26\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--58\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b722\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-721\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-580\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b580\"><table><tbody><tr><td><span>New wines in the door!</span><p><strong><span><span><span>Pillitteri Estate Vidal Icewine</span></span></span><span>: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>If you've never had one, Icewine is produced from grapes left to naturally freeze on the vine and pressed while frozen, concentrating the sugars and flavors into an intensely aromatic dessert wine! This Canadian Icewine showcases the vintage's naturally vibrant acidity, balancing its rich sweetness with freshness and elegance. Aromas of stone fruit and wildflower honey lead into a luscious palate layered with pineapple and orange peel.</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b724\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b416\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/497ff9d4-b9cd-14cd-079c-405d7dc716d1.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/497ff9d4-b9cd-14cd-079c-405d7dc716d1.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-415\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b415\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Wine we’re drinking this week:<p><span><span><span>It's officially pool season! I know pool season started weeks ago for some of you, but I made my first trip to the pool this past weekend - along with what felt like half the county. I saw many of you there at KoC. (Yes, that was me having a splash fight with Beth's 9-year-old.) Those of you who are pool veterans know that pre-loading your Owala is key to optimizing your pool experience. And we've got an entire wall of crispy white wines just waiting and ready to hit the pool with you.<br><br>Last week, we debuted </span></span></span><strong><span><span><span>Basa Lore Igartzeta Txakoli</span></span></span></strong><span><span><span> on our shelves and let me tell you - this hit perfectly last weekend in the heat. As you may know, Txakoli is best known for being poured in a celebratory arc from a pitcher. It's also known for being bone dry, thirst quenchingly acidic, and slightly sparkling. Basa Lore Igartzeta is all of those things plus notes of green apple, fresh flowers, and crisp salinity. That touch of sparkling is perfect to emphasize the freshness and, frankly, fun of this wine. So grab a bottle of Txakoli and get locked and loaded for your next pool outing, or neighborhood gathering, or patio night.</span></span></span></p><p><em><span><span><span><span>This week’s writeup is brought to you by Julie.</span></span></span></span></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b508\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-452\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b452\"><table id=\"section_01bf9123c72b4273c09973c86654fac7\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--37\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-10\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--50\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b456\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-455\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b453\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/20b93579-3245-f13b-fea6-acd8c179912c.jpeg\" width=\"534\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/20b93579-3245-f13b-fea6-acd8c179912c.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"533.8\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:533.8px;width:533.8px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-454\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b454\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span>June Tasting Events coming your way!</span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b457\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gu